  "chapter": {
    "number": 28,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Captivity of Ephraim"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Woe to the majestic crown of Ephraim’s",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2605
          },
          {
            "text": "drunkards,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the fading flower of his glorious splendor,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "set on the summit above the fertile valley,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the pride of those overcome by wine.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the Lord has one",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who is strong and mighty.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Like a hailstorm or destructive tempest,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a driving rain or flooding downpour,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he will smash that crown to the ground.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The majestic crown of Ephraim’s drunkards",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be trampled underfoot.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fading flower of his beautiful splendor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "set on the summit above the fertile valley,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will be like a ripe fig before the summer harvest:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Whoever sees it will take it in his hand and swallow it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day the LORD of Hosts will be a crown of glory,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a diadem of splendor to the remnant of His people,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "a spirit of justice to him who sits in judgment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a strength to those who repel the onslaught at the gate.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "These also stagger from wine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and stumble from strong drink:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Priests and prophets reel from strong drink",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and are befuddled by wine.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They stumble because of strong drink,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "muddled in their visions and stumbling in their judgments.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For all their tables are covered with vomit;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is not a place without filth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whom is He trying to teach?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "To whom is He explaining His message?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "To infants just weaned from milk?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "To babies removed from the breast?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they hear:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2606
          },
          {
            "text": "“Order on order, order on order,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "line on line, line on line;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2607
          },
          {
            "text": "a little here, a little there.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, with mocking lips and foreign tongues,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will speak to this people",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2608
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "to whom He has said:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“This is the place of rest, let the weary rest;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "this is the place of repose.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "But they would not listen.",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the word of the LORD to them will become:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Order on order, order on order,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "line on line, line on line;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a little here, a little there,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that they will go stumbling backward",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will be injured, ensnared, and captured.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Cornerstone in Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore hear the word of the LORD, O scoffers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who rule this people in Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you said, “We have made a covenant with death;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we have fashioned an agreement with Sheol.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When the overwhelming scourge passes through",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will not touch us,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because we have made lies our refuge",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and falsehood",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2609
          },
          {
            "text": "our hiding place.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "So this is what the Lord GOD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“See, I lay a stone in Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a tested stone,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a precious cornerstone, a sure foundation;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the one who believes will never be shaken.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2610
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make justice the measuring line",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and righteousness the level.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Hail will sweep away your refuge of lies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and water will flood your hiding place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your covenant with death will be dissolved,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your agreement with Sheol will not stand.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When the overwhelming scourge passes through,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will be trampled by it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As often as it passes through,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will carry you away;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it will sweep through morning after morning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "by day and by night.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "The understanding of this message",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will bring sheer terror.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, the bed is too short to stretch out on,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the blanket too small to wrap around you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the LORD will rise up as at Mount Perazim.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will rouse Himself as in the Valley of Gibeon,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to do His work, His strange work,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to perform His task, His disturbing task.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So now, do not mock,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or your shackles will become heavier.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, I have heard from the Lord GOD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a decree of destruction against the whole land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Listen and Hear"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen and hear my voice.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Pay attention and hear what I say.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Does the plowman plow for planting every day?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Does he continuously loosen and harrow the soil?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When he has leveled its surface,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "does he not sow caraway and scatter cumin?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He plants wheat in rows and barley in plots,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rye within its border.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For his God instructs",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and teaches him properly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely caraway is not threshed with a sledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the wheel of a cart is not rolled over the cumin.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But caraway is beaten out with a stick,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and cumin with a rod.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Grain for bread must be ground,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but it is not endlessly threshed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Though the wheels of the cart roll over it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the horses do not crush it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This also comes from the LORD of Hosts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who is wonderful in counsel",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and excellent in wisdom.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
